---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Barometer from '../components/Barometer.astro';
import barometer from '../data/barometer.json';

// Donations are intentionally NOT live yet (decision 2026-07-11): the page
// only shows the concept. Once PayPal/IBAN/Sponsors accounts exist, replace
// the "coming soon" chips below with real links.
---

<Base title="Donate" description="Cardo is free. Voluntary donations cover the year's running costs – shown transparently as a percentage, never as amounts.">
  <h1>Support Cardo</h1>
  <p class="muted">
    Cardo is free and will stay free. No paywall, no premium tier, no “pro” version. If Cardo
    gives you a calmer place, and you want to give something back – this is where you can.
  </p>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
    <h2>Why donations?</h2>
    <p>
      Even a local-first app has a few real-world bills: the domain, signing certificates
      (Apple charges 99 €/year), a small server for the optional sync feature, and a couple of
      infrastructure tools. Donations exist to cover exactly these costs – nothing more is asked for.
    </p>
    <h3>Where we stand for {barometer.year}</h3>
    <Barometer />
    <p class="muted">{barometer.note}</p>
  </section>

  <section class="ways">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>PayPal</h3>
      <p>One-off or recurring, whatever suits you.</p>
      <p><span class="soon">Coming soon</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Bank transfer</h3>
      <p>No fees, works from any European bank account.</p>
      <p><span class="soon">Coming soon</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>GitHub Sponsors</h3>
      <p>If you're on GitHub anyway.</p>
      <p><span class="soon">Coming soon</span></p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <p class="muted">
    Donation options aren't set up yet – Cardo is brand new. Until they are, the best support
    is simple: use Cardo and tell us in the forum what works and what doesn't.
  </p>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top:2rem">
    <h3>The honest fine print</h3>
    <p>
      We publish only the percentage of costs covered – never absolute amounts, and never who
      donated. Once 100 % is reached, the barometer disappears and we say so openly: from that
      point on, further donations go personally to the developer. Nobody should ever feel
      pressured – Cardo works exactly the same whether you donate or not.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .ways { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
    .ways h3 { margin-top: 0; }
    .soon {
      display: inline-block; background: var(--surface-1); color: var(--text-muted);
      border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.35rem 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
